5174 VOID
5175 FsRtlPrivateResetLowestLockOffset (
5176  PLOCK_INFO LockInfo
5177  )
5178 
5179 /*++
5180 
5181 Routine Description:
5182 
5183  This routine resets the lowest lock offset hint in a LOCK_INFO to
5184  the lowest lock offset currently held by a lock inside of the LOCK_INFO.
5185 
5186 Arguments:
5187 
5188  LockInfo - the lock data to operate on
5189 
5190 Return Value:
5191 
5192  None
5193 
5194 --*/
5195 
5196 {
5197  PEX_LOCK ExLock = NULL;
5198  PSH_LOCK ShLock = NULL;
5199  PFILE_LOCK_INFO LowestLockInfo = NULL;
5200  PRTL_SPLAY_LINKS SplayLinks;
5201  PLOCKTREE_NODE Node;
5202 
5203  //
5204  // Fix up the lowest lock offset if we have non-empty trees and there was
5205  // a lock in the low 32 bit region
5206  //
5207 
5208  if (LockInfo->LowestLockOffset != 0xffffffff &&
5209  (LockInfo->LockQueue.SharedLockTree != NULL ||
5210  LockInfo->LockQueue.ExclusiveLockTree != NULL)) {

5214  //

5219

5221

5224 
5225  Node = CONTAINING_RECORD( SplayLinks, LOCKTREE_NODE, Links );

5233  while (RtlLeftChild(SplayLinks) != NULL) {
5234

5237 
5238  ExLock = CONTAINING_RECORD( SplayLinks, EX_LOCK, Links );
5239  }

5243  // trees at least has a lock, so if we have don't have exclusive locks then we do know
5244  // we have shared locks ...
5245  //
5246 
5247  if (ExLock &&
5248  (!ShLock ||
5249  (ULONGLONG)ExLock->LockInfo.StartingByte.QuadPart < (ULONGLONG)ShLock->LockInfo.StartingByte.QuadPart)) {

5263

5265  }
5266 
5267  } else {

5278 NTSTATUS
5279 FsRtlPrivateFastUnlockAll (

5287 
5288 /*++
5289 
5290 Routine Description:
5291 
5292  This routine performs an Unlock all operation on the current locks
5293  associated with the specified file lock. Only those locks with
5294  a matching file object and process id are freed. Additionally,
5295  it is possible to free only those locks which also match a given
5296  key.
5297 
5298 Arguments:
5299 
5300  FileLock - Supplies the file lock being freed.
5301 
5302  FileObject - Supplies the file object associated with the file lock
5303 
5304  ProcessId - Supplies the Process Id associated with the locks to be
5305  freed
5306 
5307  Key - Supplies the Key to use in this operation
5308 
5309  MatchKey - Whether or not the Key must also match for lock to be freed.
5310 
5311  Context - Supplies an optional context to use when completing waiting
5312  lock irps.
5313 
5314 Return Value:
5315 
5316  None
5317 
5318 --*/
5319 
5320 {
5321  PLOCK_INFO LockInfo;
5322  PLOCK_QUEUE LockQueue;
5323  PSINGLE_LIST_ENTRY *pLink, *SavepLink, Link;
5324  NTSTATUS NewStatus;
5325  KIRQL OldIrql;
5326  LARGE_INTEGER GlueOffset, EndingDeletedByte;

5328  PSH_LOCK ShLock = NULL;

5331  PLOCKTREE_NODE Node;
5332

5334  DebugTrace(+1, Dbg, "FsRtlPrivateFastUnlockAll, FileLock = %08lx\n", FileLock);
5335

5337 
5338  //
5339  // No lock information on this FileLock
5340  //
5341 
5342  DebugTrace(+1, Dbg, "FsRtlPrivateFastUnlockAll, No LockInfo\n", FileLock);
5343  return STATUS_RANGE_NOT_LOCKED;
5344  }
5345 
5346  FileObject->LastLock = NULL;
5347 
5348  LockQueue = &LockInfo->LockQueue;
5349 
5350  //
5351  // Grab the waiting lock queue spinlock to exclude anyone from messing
5352  // with the queue while we're using it
5353  //
5354 
5355  FsRtlAcquireLockQueue( LockQueue, &OldIrql );
5356 
5357  if (LockQueue->SharedLockTree == NULL && LockQueue->ExclusiveLockTree == NULL) {
5358 
5359  //
5360  // No locks on this FileLock
5361  //
5362 
5363  DebugTrace(+1, Dbg, "FsRtlPrivateFastUnlockAll, No LockTrees\n", FileLock);
5364  FsRtlReleaseLockQueue( LockQueue, OldIrql );
5365 
5366  return STATUS_RANGE_NOT_LOCKED;
5367  }
5368 
5369  //
5370  // Remove all matching locks in the shared lock tree
5371  //
5372 
5373  if (LockQueue->SharedLockTree != NULL) {
5374 
5375  //
5376  // Grab the lowest node in the tree
5377  //
5378 
5379  SplayLinks = LockQueue->SharedLockTree;
5380 
5381  while (RtlLeftChild(SplayLinks) != NULL) {
5382 
5383  SplayLinks = RtlLeftChild(SplayLinks);
5384  }
5385 
5386  //
5387  // Walk all nodes in the tree
5388  //
5389 
5390  UnlockRoutine = FALSE;
5391

5394  SplayLinks = SuccessorLinks) {
5395 
5396  Node = CONTAINING_RECORD(SplayLinks, LOCKTREE_NODE, Links );
5397 
5398  //

5400  // of deleting locks. It would be a waste of time to traverse those split
5401  // nodes. The only case in which we will not have traversed the entire list
5402  // before doing the split will be if there is an unlock routine attached
5403  // to this FileLock in which case we will be restarting the entire scan
5404  // anyway.
5405  //
5406 
5407  SuccessorLinks = RtlRealSuccessor(SplayLinks);
5408

5411  // the file object and process id
5412  //

5776 
5777  This routine implements the cancel function for an irp saved in a
5778  waiting lock queue
5779 
5780 Arguments:
5781 
5782  DeviceObject - Ignored

5789 
5790  none.
5791

5793 
5794 {

5796  PLOCK_INFO LockInfo;
5797  PLOCK_QUEUE LockQueue;
5798  KIRQL OldIrql;
5799  NTSTATUS NewStatus;

5807  // containing the irp

5814  //

5833  //

5836  pLink = &FsRtlFileLockCancelCollideList.Next;
5837 
5838  } else {
5839 
5840  OldIrql = Irp->CancelIrql;
5841 
5842  //
5843  // We will iterate only the locks off of this specific queue.
5844  //
5845 
5846  pLink = &LockQueue->WaitingLocks.Next;
5847  }
5848 
5849  while (TRUE) {
5850 
5851  //
5852  // Iterate through the waiting locks looking for the canceled one.
5853  //

5856

5858

5945  //
